            <p>June 5th&#44; 5650<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr Piza called on me<lb/> this evening and informed me&#44;<lb/> to my great grief and regret&#44;<lb/> that you had called at the Sem&#45;<lb/>&#45;inary and found it closed.<lb/>  I am sorry&#44; indeed&#44; that you<lb/> should have made such a trip in<lb/> vain but&#44; as you will see by the<lb/> enclosed curriculum&#44; the Semin&#45;<lb/>&#45;ary is now having its vacation of<lb/> four weeks after the close of the<lb/> long term.  The instructions<lb/> of the curriculum as fixed by<lb/> the conjoint Advisory Board and<lb/> Seminary Committee are being<lb/> carried out and it would have<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>been impossible for us to de&#45;<lb/>&#45;viate therefrom&#44; in the absence<lb/> of specific orders.  On June 15th<lb/> at 3 P. M. we reopen for the<lb/> short term.  Perhaps I may<lb/> go to Philadelphia next Sunday<lb/> and then might be able to<lb/> confer with you personally&#44;<lb/> I remain&#44; with sincere regrets<lb/> for your disappointment<lb/> very truly yours<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>From<lb/>
                329 E 51st St<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. 5th St<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
